-- Telecinco to Raise EU499 Million in Share Sale for Pay-TV Deal
-- B y   P a u l   T o b i n
-- 2010-11-18T08:22:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-18/telecinco-announces-plan-to-raise-678-1-million-through-rights-offering.html
Gestevision Telecinco SA (TL5) , Spainâ€™s
largest commercial television station, said it will raise 499
million euros ($678 million) to finance the purchase of a stake
in pay-TV company Digital Plus.  Telecinco will offer investors 5 new shares for every 14
owned at 5.75 euros each, the Madrid-based broadcaster said
today in a regulatory filing. Parent  Mediaset SpA (MS)  will buy its
proportional shares, Telecinco said.  Telecinco is buying 22 percent of Digital Plus from
 Promotora de Informaciones SA , or Prisa, and has also agreed to
purchase free-to-air channel Cuatro from the media company. To
pay for Cuatro, Telecinco will give Prisa new shares mounting to
an 18 percent stake in the company. The details of the second
capital increase have yet to be disclosed.  JPMorgan Chase & Co., Mediobanca SpA, Banca IMI SpA and
Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA are managing the rights
offering, Telecinco said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
